      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content</head>
         <p>This is an artificial collection of correspondence and manuscripts by members of the
            beat generation assembled by curators and staff of the Rare Book &amp; Manuscript
            Library. The collection includes manuscripts by writers such as LeRoi Jones, Claude
            Pelieu, and Thomas McGrath as well as pieces of correspondence written by Neal Cassady
            (to Ken Kesey) and Gary Snyder.</p>
         <p/>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>This collection is arranged in 1 series: Series 1: Correspondence and Manuscripts,
            1959-1971.</p>
      </arrangement>
